@NODE "datasheet" "clicktab_gc/datasheet (information)"


    NAME
        clicktab.gadget--File folder tabs gadget.

    SUPERCLASS
        gadgetclass

    REQUIRES
        None.

    DESCRIPTION
        The tabs gadget class provides a custom control that has imagry
        similar in style to the tabs seen in a drawer full of file folders.
        The action of the gadget is the same as a conventional
        mutual-exclusion control in that only one tab can be active at a
        time and a tab is selected by clicking upon it.

        The purpose of the tabs gadget class is to provide functionality like
        the page selection cycle gadget on the top-right side of the AmigaOS
        2.1 PrinterPS preferences editor, but allowing all the choices to be
        visible at the same time. The tab "bar" allows strumming across the
        selections. The current selection is slightly raised and its text
        label displayed in bold.

    METHODS
        @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63} -- Create the button gadget.  Passed to superclass, then @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}.

        @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66} -- Get an object attribute.  Passed to superclass for unknown
            attributes.

        @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} -- Set object attributes.  Passed to superclass first.

        @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70} -- Set object notification attributes.  Passed to superclass
            first.

        @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69} -- Sets  taglist for notification and pass to superclass.

        @{"GM_DOMAIN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 323} -- Calculate imagery & positioning, and return
            minimum/maximum domain size.

        @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302} -- Renders the gadget imagry.  Overrides the superclass.

        @{"GM_HITTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 298} -- Determines if mouse is within the gadget rectangle.
            Overrides the superclass.

        @{"GM_GOACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 305} -- Handles activation, toggle-select and button-select.
            Overrides the superclass.

        @{"GM_GOINACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 311} -- Deactivates object.  Overrides the superclass.

        @{"GM_HANDLEINPUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 308} -- Handles selection input, RMB undo/abort, etc.

        GM_KEYACTIVE -- Activates gadget via keyboard, selects appropriate
            tab based on input key.  Invoked by window.class only.

        GM_KEYINACTIVE -- Deactivates gadget.  Invoked by window.class only.

        @{"GM_HELPTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 314} -- Handles gadget help. When the mouse is over a tab,
            the method returns @{"GMR_HELPCODE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 372} along with the tabindex. Before
            v45 @{"GMR_HELPHIT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 371} was the only return value besides 0L, also
            before v45 this method didn't return a reliabel result in all cases.

        All other methods are passed to the superclass, including @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64}.

